      <prefercite id="aspace_539e36c811e9d351bfa3d067f703309c">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>John Morton Blum Papers (MS 86). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_014de72f1978b5443355e1b574f0bd31">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of John Morton Blum, 1966, 1985, 1991, 1994-1997, 2005, 2007, and 2009. Gift of Lewis L. Gould, 2016-2017.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_60fa86f01d0e403778b6dce89ff030e1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>John Morton Blum (A.B. Harvard 1943, M.A. 1947, Ph.D. 1950) was a research associate, assistant professor of history, and associate professor at M.I.T. from 1948-1957. He has been a professor of history at Yale since 1957. Blum died on October 18, 2011, in North Branford, Connecticut.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_155cfd8a6f6f0577b1d7536e63f60462">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Collection is arranged by accessions.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_b49571de95d75dde2859db0df43165fe">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_e32836250aed5c49e75ab4f73b130b4e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of typescript drafts and research notes for three published works: <title render="italic">
               <part>Joe Tumulty and the Wilson Era</part>
            </title>; <title render="italic">
               <part>Woodrow Wilson and the Politics of Morality</part>
            </title>; and <title render="italic">
               <part>The Promise of America</part>
            </title>. Also included is some professional and personal correspondence.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <userestrict id="aspace_6d411165ba7e4b70d72617a73f95d9c7">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
